(ns rams-ui.ajax
  (:require [ajax.core :refer [GET POST PUT]]
            [rams-ui.util :refer [gen-uuid rendering-id set-db-value
                                  set-value get-value get-db-value]]
            [reagent-material-ui.core.circular-progress :refer [circular-progress]]
            [reagent-material-ui.core.linear-progress :refer [linear-progress]]))


(defn ajax-loader
  [{:keys [id type] :as config}]
  (let [uuid (if id id :rams-ui|-|loader)
        state (get-value uuid :persistent? true)]
    (when @state
      [(if (= :type :bar)
         linear-progress
         circular-progress)
       (dissoc config :type :id)])))


(let [ajax-call-count (atom 0)
      loader-count (atom 0)
      repeating-requests (atom {})
      config (atom {:success "success"
                    :error "error"
                    :warning "error"
                    :method :get})]
  
  (defn set-config
    "a helper function to configure the ajax call. It takes the following keys:

    - **key**: is one of the following keywords:
      - **:success**: identifies the string value of the key :success in an api request which identifies if a request if successful or not. Default is \"success\"
      - **:error**: identifies the string value of the key :success in an api request which identifies if a request if error or not. Default is \"error\"
      - **:warning**: identifies the string value of the key :success in an api request which identifies if a request if warning or not. Default is \"warning\"
      - **:method**: keyword that identifies the default REST method to use and can be either :get | :post | :put. Default is :get"
    [key value]
    (swap! config #(assoc % key value)))
  
  (defn make-call [& {:keys [on-success-fn on-error-fn
                             on-warning-fn on-finally-fn
                             show-loader? call-key
                             url  method params
                             no-repeat-response-fn
                             required-message-fn
                             handle-message-fn
                             loader-id]
                      :or {method (:method @config)}}]
    (let [id (if loader-id
               loader-id
               :rams-ui|-|loader)]
      (if (or (not (contains? @repeating-requests call-key))
              (not no-repeat-response-fn))
        (do
          (swap! repeating-requests #(assoc %
                                            call-key true))
          (when show-loader?
            (set-value id true :persistent? true)
            (swap! loader-count inc))
          (swap! ajax-call-count inc)
          ((case method
             :post POST
             :put PUT
             GET) url
           {:params params
            :headers {"Accept" "application/transit+json"}
            :handler (fn [{:keys [status message] :as result}]
                       (when (and status message (fn? handle-message-fn))
                         (handle-message-fn result))
                       (when (or (nil? status)
                                 (= status (:success @config)))
                         (when (fn? on-success-fn)
                           (on-success-fn result)))
                       (when (= status (:warning @config))
                         (if (fn? on-warning-fn)
                           (on-warning-fn result)
                           (when (fn? on-success-fn)
                             (on-success-fn result))))
                       (when (= status (:error @config))
                         (if (fn? on-error-fn)
                           (on-error-fn result)
                           (when (and (nil? message)
                                      (fn? required-message-fn))
                             (required-message-fn result)))))
            :finally (fn []
                       (swap! ajax-call-count dec)
                       (swap! loader-count dec)
                       (when (= @loader-count 0)
                         (set-value id false :persistent? true))
                       (swap! repeating-requests #(dissoc % call-key))
                       (when (fn? on-finally-fn)
                         (on-finally-fn)))
            :error-handler (fn [result]
                             (when (fn? on-error-fn)
                               (on-error-fn result)))}))
        (when (fn? no-repeat-response-fn)
          (no-repeat-response-fn))))))
